716f630630ab39673b1f12cb9c72689406a0a354.summary: Configure SDL assuming we, in fact, have a libc.
716f630630ab39673b1f12cb9c72689406a0a354.body:
Without this, on Linux and Linux alone, and only if SDL is builtin, the
definitions for some functions - notably, memset/memcpy - are taken from
SDL source.

This leaves them at the mercy of the compiler and may lead to the
optimal implementations of these functions not being selected. But the
main motivation for this is that it's action at a distance that is
incredibly surprising - linking in a gamepad support library should not
change the implementation of memset/memcpy!

368588ce6d31fc2879f32e506960ff34324f3526.summary: iOS: Fix loading of xcframework dynamic libraries.
368588ce6d31fc2879f32e506960ff34324f3526.body:
The logic used to determine whether to invoke the in-memory registration or to
delegate the loading of a library is incorrect for xcframework packages - as
these can contain either static or dynamic libraries.

This change instead lets the operating system handle the library request, and if
it fails, it attempts to load from the internal registry.

With this change, xcframeworks containing dynamic libraries work without
workarounds on iOS.

With an additional fallback case courtesy of @bruvzg

This fixes https://github.com/godotengine/godot/issues/112783

(cherry picked from commit b1465d6af088abd9771cd8a0c087d4e8b141c884)
